"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1943081-paralympics-cheating-row-explodes-paris-2024\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"A cheating row at this summer's Paralympic games in Paris has erupted with one athlete stripped of his medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 59, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998933617, \"rank\": 1.0668760092335344e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A cheating row\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 14}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's Paralympic games\", \"from\": 18, \"to\": 48}, {\"ngram\": \"one athlete\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 86}, {\"ngram\": \"his medal\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italian Giacomo Perini was disqualified from the final of the PR1 single sculls, with Australian Erik Horrie bumped up into the bronze medal position.\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 113, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9949198547232969, \"rank\": 0.0043087229042883726, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 199, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9971653905678359, \"rank\": 0.0024668236820961477, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 210, \"end\": 221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_Horrie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erik Horrie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_Horrie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_Horrie\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the final\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 167}, {\"ngram\": \"the PR1 single sculls\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 192}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal position\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 262}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Horrie joinedTeam GB'sBenjamin Pritchard and Ukrainian Roman Polianskyi on the podium, but it wasn't without controversy at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium in the French capital.\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language\", \"score\": 0.7262473237948359, \"rank\": 0.3705752466272529, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.357236239101241e-14, \"text\": \"Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\"}, {\"begin\": 434, \"end\": 440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9914244401432271, \"rank\": 0.004777258785323555, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Horrie joinedTeam GB'sBenjamin Pritchard\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 305}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 350}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's claimed the Italian athlete was disqualified for using a communication device during the race, which is said to have been a mobile phone - something outlawed across the board at both the Paralympic and Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 468, \"end\": 475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9949198547232969, \"rank\": 0.0043087229042883726, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a communication device\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"a mobile phone\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 592}, {\"ngram\": \"- something\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"the board\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"both the Paralympic and Olympic Games\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Race officials verified a device had been found and was used, with it then announced Perini had been booted out of the medal standings shortly after.\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Race officials\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"a device\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 706}, {\"ngram\": \"Perini\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal standings\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 808}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An investigation has been launched by officials in Paris, with a statement released by World Rowing reading: \\\"In the final of the PR1 M1x, the ITA PR1 MRX was found to be using communications equipment during the race, in breach of Rule 28 and Appendix R2, Bye-Law to Rule 28.\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998933617, \"rank\": 1.0668760092335344e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Rowing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 955, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Runestone_styles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"PR1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Runestone_styles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Runestone_styles\"}, {\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"MRX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\"}, {\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"score\": 0.9869077597995988, \"rank\": 0.013217586509156271, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An investigation\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 872}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"the final\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 947}, {\"ngram\": \"communications equipment\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"breach\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"Rule\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"Bye-Law\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As a result, the crew has been excluded from the event and will be ranked last.\\\"\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"the crew\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1158}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy's rowing authority were next to chime in, claiming the rower had forgotten his phone had been left in the boat prior to the race starting.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9676678421415628, \"rank\": 0.03339398390468976, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rower\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"his phone\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"the boat\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A post shared by FederazioneItalianaCanottaggio (@canottaggio1888) The governing body commented via anInstagrampost: \\\"After a historic and highly competitive competition, ending with an exciting third place and a bronze medal, while everyone was celebrating the achievement, the Jury was excluded from the Paralympic podium of the PR1 single for this reason: 'In the final Men's singles PR1, the Italian athlete was found using communication equipment during the race, in violation of rule 28 and Appendix R2, Bye-Law of rule 28.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1729, \"end\": 1736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9949198547232969, \"rank\": 0.0043087229042883726, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"score\": 0.9869077597995988, \"rank\": 0.013217586509156271, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A post\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"FederazioneItalianaCanottaggio\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 137